snippet.textDisplay:
tl;dr: Switch Lite is going to sell more than the regular Switch in December, and games are going to suffer for it. Also, Metroid, buy everything Metroid.

Maybe my 14 years of retail experience (not there anymore thank goodness) isn't worth too much, but if anyone thinks that the Nintendo Switch Lite isn't going to sell like crazy in the holiday season they're probably wrong. The Boxing Week deal won't be anything spectacular, though, maybe $10-20 off, or come bundled with a game nobody cares about. If that's what you see for Black Friday, that's what you'll probably get for Boxing Week.

Every parent that hears "I want a Switch" is going to get their kid the Lite version unless they want to play it themselves too. Or parents that got the previous Switch for their kid(s) and discovered they liked it too will buy their kid the Switch Lite so they can keep one in the living room for themselves. Or for many people, the Lite will hit a price that parents are willing to spend to make their kids happy, when before the cost was prohibitive. Nintendo is absolutely positioning this to replace the 3DS series of handhelds.

The not-really-a-Switch-anymore Lite is going to become such a sudden large portion of the install base that game developers won't feel encouraged to focus time on developing for the Joy-Con's features, or outright just ditch them if they're not fleshed out before crunch time, hurting creativity and consumer play options. :(

PS: I don't own a Switch yet, I'm probably the only loser waiting for the new Metroid Prime to come out before I buy one. Everyone should play Metroid games. Buy them. Love them. You want to. Please. Except Other M. Yoshio Sakamoto should be banned from Metroid forever. I need moar Metroid in my life. Metroid.

PPS: Since you're still reading, somehow, if Nintendo ever did make a Switch Pro: I think a no-screen console-only version would sell well if they called it Wii Switch, and if they brought back a lot of Wii era stuff they could bring that market in. That could justify making it also be a bit more gamer-friendly too. I feel dirty for suggesting it, but it feels like a Nintendo thing to do.
